==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tax certificate
<hw>Tax certificate</hw>. <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The certificate issued
to the purchaser of land at a tax sale certifying to the sale and the
payment of the consideration thereof, and entitling the purchaser upon
certain conditions and at a certain time thereafter to a deed or
instrument of conveyance (called a <xex>tax deed</xex>) of the land, to
be executed by the proper officer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Taxel</ent>⟦br⟧
